trans-unit.source: Note: On Linux and macOS, the drag and drop operation can take some time, but this function does not block the event loop. Other events are still delivered to the application while the operation is performed. On Windows, the Qt event loop is blocked during the operation.
trans-unit.target: 注意：在Linux和macOS上，拖放操作可能需要一些时间，但是此功能不会阻止事件循环。在执行操作时，其他事件仍会传递到应用程序。在Windows上，该操作期间Qt事件循环被阻止。

trans-unit.source: Note: On Linux and macOS, the drag and drop operation can take some time, but this function does not block the event loop. Other events are still delivered to the application while the operation is performed. On Windows, the Qt event loop is blocked during the operation. However, QDrag::exec() on Windows causes processEvents() to be called frequently to keep the GUI responsive. If any loops or operations are called while a drag operation is active, it will block the drag operation.
trans-unit.target: 注意：在Linux和macOS上，拖放操作可能需要一些时间，但是此功能不会阻止事件循环。在执行操作时，其他事件仍会传递到应用程序。在Windows上，该操作期间Qt事件循环被阻止。但是，Windows上的QDrag :: exec（）导致processEvents（）被频繁调用以保持GUI响应。如果在拖动操作处于活动状态时调用了任何循环或操作，它将阻止拖动操作。

Note: On Linux and macOS, the drag and drop operation can take some time, but this function does not block the event loop. Other events are still delivered to the application while the operation is performed. On Windows, the Qt event loop is blocked during the operation. However, QDrag::exec() on Windows causes processEvents() to be called frequently to keep the GUI responsive. If any loops or operations are called while a drag operation is active, it will block the drag operation.
